Doing a full-time job as a software engineer means most days are already packed before I even think of doing anything else. Filling, editing, planning—it’s hard to squeeze it all in.

But one promise I’ve kept to myself is not missing the gym more than twice a week.
This one day, I got back home around 10 pm, completely exhausted after work… and I still went. Just showed up. That’s it. That’s the win.

Honestly, I’m just super proud of being consistent with one habit.
It’s not always easy—it feels bad sometimes, like I’m not doing enough in other areas.
But I’m way more consistent than I used to be, and honestly? That’s all that matters. That’s growth.

Rest of the week—I’m just keeping up. Caught up on some news, started The Midnight Library, and made space for some self-care. Hair, skin, mental health—the little stuff that keeps me feeling like me.

Some weeks are for thriving. Some are for surviving. But this week—I showed up for myself. And that counts 🤍
